LUMPY SKIN DISEASE - BULGARIA (07): BOVINE, SPREAD, INTERNATIONAL IMPACT
************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Mon 9 May 2016
Source: Monitor Bulgaria [in Bulgarian, machine trans., edited] http://tinyurl.com/hb6jvgp


Farmers from the villages Belovitsa, Malo Krusevo and Krasnovo blocked this morning for about 2 hours the road to Plovdiv and Strelcha. Protesters want to get the cattle vaccines against nodular dermatitis [Lumpy skin disease, LSD], the earliest. This infectious cow disease was discovered in Belovitsa, where 82 cows and calves were killed and buried on 7 May 2016.

"The state is doing everything possible. In addition to the 1st consignment of 150 000 vaccine doses, 170 000 additional doses of the vaccine will arrive on 16 May and will be immediately applied. I met personally with the protesters and explained to them, but they have a right to worry about the health of the animals, because the movement of the disease is uncontrollable. We do not know how this occurs and where, but what the state is currently doing is adequate and as quickly as possible, "said the head of the Regional Directorate of the Agency for Food, Dr. Kamen Yankov.

According to him, the 1st batch of the vaccine was introduced on the 15th day since the announcement of the disease. The 2nd phase of vaccination will be after 16 May. Other animals in the village Belovitsa will not be killed, said Dr. Yankov. "We have no grounds," he said. On Monday [9 May 2016] it found a suspected case in the village of Trilistnik, confirmed Dr. Yankov. In his words, a sample was taken from the cow, the results of which will become clear on Tuesday [10 May 2016].

[Byline: Eli Krumova]

